  Compare Project / Circuits / Panda solvers on standard test grids.
  Press Ctrl-C at any time to exit.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[Step 1] Grid
  1. IEEE 14-bus
  2. WB5  (Bukhsh 2013 — non-convex bottleneck, SOCP duality gap)
  3. Case22loop — uniform costs ($2/MWh, exact SOCP)
  4. Case22loop — asymmetric costs ($1/$4 split, multiple local optima)
Enter choice [1-4]: 
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[Step 2] Solvers to run  (comma-separated, or Enter for all)
  1. Circuits NR    (Newton-Raphson AC power flow)
  2. Project DC OPF (cvxpy linear DC OPF)
  3. Project SOCP   (SOCP relaxation — OPF mode for this grid)
  4. Panda DC OPF   (linear DC OPF)
  5. Panda AC OPF   (interior-point AC OPF — slow)
Enter numbers (e.g. 1,3 — or Enter for all): 
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Loading modules...
  Grid: WB5

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[Step 3] Generator costs
  Default costs for this grid:
    GenSlack: $4.00/MWh
    GenPV: $1.00/MWh
  Use defaults? [Y/n]: 
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[Step 4] Metrics to display  (comma-separated, or Enter for all)
  1. Voltage magnitudes  (pu)
  2. Voltage angles      (deg)
  3. Branch P flows      (from-end, pu)
  4. Branch Q flows      (from-end, pu)
  5. Objective value     ($/h)
  6. Convergence status
  7. Solve time          (s)
  8. SOCP tightness      (τ per branch)
  9. Loop residuals      (deg, meshed networks only)
Enter numbers (e.g. 1,5,6 — or Enter for all): 
